          <ul>
            <li><strong>No battery maintenance</strong> - Uses city water pressure</li>
            <li><strong>Unlimited runtime</strong> - Works as long as water pressure exists</li>
            <li><strong>Simple mechanism</strong> - Fewer parts to fail</li>
            <li><strong>Higher water usage</strong> - Uses 1 gallon city water per 2 gallons pumped</li>
            <li><strong>Requires adequate pressure</strong> - Needs 40+ PSI to function</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Homes with excellent water pressure, backup to battery systems</p>
          <p><strong>Investment:</strong> $300-$600 for pump only</p>

